# **Casting Call ‚Äì Vancouver Laser & Skin Care Centre**

Hi everyone!
We are currently casting talent for **vertical ads **to promote our upcoming **February & March campaign**.

## **Roles Needed**
* **2 talents (male & female)**
* **Age:** 25‚Äì35
* **Ethnicity:** Caucasian or East Asian
* **Language:** Native-level English fluency
* **Preferred (not required):** Experience with social media content, beauty industry, or ad shoots

##  **Project Details**
* **Deliverables:** 6‚Äì9 vertical videos (approx. 15-second ads)
* **Shoot Duration:** 3.5‚Äì4 hours (approx.)
* **Shoot Date:** 
For the **February Shooting**: One day between **January 21-23** (exact date TBC)
For the **March Shooting**: One day between **February 16-25** (exact date TBC)
* **Location**: 750 W Broadway 3rd Floor, Vancouver, BC V5Z 1H2
* **Wardrobe & Makeup:** Not provided ‚Äî please dress in **business-casual style**

##  **Compensation**
* **$300 flat rate**
* **One BBL or PicoWay Treatment**
* **Snacks & coffee provided** 

## **How to Apply**

Please email the following to **ben@vancouverlaser.com**
**Subject line:** *February/March Campaign + [Your Name]*
* Headshot
* Resume
* Demo videos (if available)

**Please note that private messages will not be replied to**.

If you have any questions, feel free to reach out.
We look forward to your submissions!

items.text:
**CASTING CALL ‚Äì AMBER (LEAD ROLE)**

**Short Film | Psychological Drama / Tech Thriller**

Hello everyone,

We‚Äôre reopening casting for the **lead role of Amber** due to an unexpected last-minute change. The actress previously cast had to step away for a paid commitment. There are no hard feelings ‚Äî we completely understand and wish her the best. This does, however, mean we‚Äôre reaching out again in hopes of finding the right person to step in and collaborate with us.
**PROJECT DETAILS**

**Project:** Short Film
**Genre:** Psychological Drama / Tech Thriller
**Shoot Location:** Lower Mainland, BC
**Shoot Date:** **Sunday, January 18th**
**Compensation:** Volunteer / Passion Project

All preparation is already in place. If you‚Äôre available and able to step in, you would genuinely be **saving the day** and helping us keep the shoot on track.
**ROLE: AMBER**

**Age Range:** 27‚Äì40
**Gender:** Female
**Ethnicity:** Open / Race-agnostic
**CHARACTER SNAPSHOT**

Amber is a high-performing Director of Sales at a tech company. Outwardly confident and disciplined, she is internally restless and unable to feel content. She is addicted to the chase‚Äîalways moving forward, never celebrating wins.

When Amber gains access to an experimental technology, she begins to rely on it too heavily. The technology destabilizes her judgment, blurring truth, error, and perception.

By the end, she withdraws from modern life‚Äînot in rebellion, but to preserve her sanity.
**PERFORMANCE NOTES**

This is a **subtle, internal performance**. We are seeking an actor who can convey psychological shifts through restraint, stillness, and micro-expression.

This is not a loud breakdown. Amber‚Äôs collapse is quiet, logical, and unsettling‚Äîdriven by over-certainty and a loss of trust in her own judgment.
**KEY TRAITS**
* Intelligent
* Controlled
* Ambitious (not arrogant)
* Emotionally guarded
* Increasingly detached
**AUDITION / SUBMISSION**

Self-tape audition
One dramatic scene (sides will be provided)

Please submit:
* Headshot
* Resume (if available)

**Email:** soultales.ca@gmail.com
**Subject:** AMBER ‚Äì Casting Submission

items.text:
*Casting Call for actors from South/West Wales*

For the production of a feature film that will be shot in Pembrokeshire this spring, with a Dutch crew and British cast, we are looking for actors for several supporting roles.

The film is about three female friends who walk the Pembrokeshire Coast Path because a fourth friend went missing there a year earlier. The journey primarily serves as a form of grieving, although mutual resentments and irritations quickly surface. It will be a drama with some thriller elements, focusing on nature and hiking.

We‚Äôre looking for:

¬∑        A male actor ‚Äì between 50 and 60 years of age

¬∑        A male actor ‚Äì 60+ years of age

¬∑        An actress ‚Äì 50+ years of age

¬∑        An actress ‚Äì 50+ years of age, fluent in Welsh

¬∑        A couple ‚Äì 65+ years of age (of course you can also apply for just one of the roles of the couple)

Filming dates will be between mid-March and mid-April. Exact dates (for each role) are yet to be determined. As the production is quite lowbudget, most of these roles are unpaid, but all expenses will be covered. Most roles will not take a full shooting day, only the older couple will be needed for a full shooting day.

We‚Äôre looking for actors who are from South/West Wales.

If you‚Äôre interested, please email us with:

- A short introduction of who you are and what acting experience you have.

- Your age and place of residence.

- One or more headshots.

- A link to your showreel or recent work.

- Your availability between mid-March and mid-April

Please email us at wales@sanderblomfilms.nl

To give you an impression of our work: below you can see the trailer for Yr Wyddfa, a short film we shot last year in North Wales. 

More of our other work (mostly in Dutch) can be found on my website: [www.sanderblomfilms.nl/vrij-werk](https://www.sanderblomfilms.nl/vrij-werk)

It‚Äôs that time again,  your chance to get your face seen! 

Drop your showreel link in the comments below, whether you‚Äôre an actor, voice-over artist, presenter, or creative, this is your space to shine. ‚ú®

You never know who might be scrolling through‚Ä¶ casting directors, agents, indie producers, someone out there could be looking for you.

‚úÖ Remember to include your name, playing age, and Spotlight or agent details (if you‚Äôve got them).

We want to encourage all our members to share their work, the more places you share your showreel, the more chances you‚Äôve got of being seen. So don‚Äôt hold back,  post it proudly!

Casting : "Maybe its love, maybe not"

I am Thomas Goersch from Stuttgart Germany. 
Actor and Filmdirector. 
I am making Independent Movies.
I present my movies on International Film festivals and was lucky to receive some awards. 
But the work is not about awards and money, its about making movies for the people to think about.
My next movie is a modern love story:
An elderly man is meeting another younger, very attractive man in the Internet.  But they are from different Continents. They start a long distance relastionship ship. which is full of passion and desire. 
One day the younger man starts to ask for money, cause he is a Student and no more able to pay his bills. 
The older man is full of distrust.
Is he only there  to pay his lovers bills or is there love between them ?
A story with two endings.
One with true love and one with betrayl.
I am looking for the young attraktive Lover.
Men  25 to 42 years old,  good looking  who is able to film his parts on his own by smartshone
I am always open and honest. You can earn no money on this. but maybe there is a good film in the end promoting for you.
I guess its not necessary that an educated actor is playing this part. so feel free to get in touch
Thats me 
www.imdb.com/name/nm1591928
Get in touch under Thomas.Goersch@vodafonemail.de 
please ask for details.

The show is a celebration to all the greatest songs and stars of the 50s 60s 70s The Beatles ,Elvis, Doris Day, Connie Francis ,Cliff Richard, Buddy Holly and more.

We are looking for drivers with cars only .
We are looking for performers on all area of the UK -please include bases when sending details.
We are offering 700 per week plus fuel on the road 
Please send details including a singing reel to info@theentertainmentproviders.co.uk

items.text:
GODSPELL ‚Äî VIDEO AUDITIONS

Wedgwood Arts

Wedgwood Arts is pleased to announce video auditions for Godspell! This non-paid production will be joyful, ensemble-driven, and thoughtfully crafted. We are seeking performers who value storytelling, collaboration, and making meaningful theatre together.

The Production team for Godspell:
Director: A. Solomon Abah Jr.
Music Direction: Adam Frame
Choreographer: (TBA) 
Stage Manager: (TBA)

PERFORMANCE DATES

April 17‚Äì19

AUDITION SUBMISSION DETAILS

Audition Deadline: Saturday, February 7 at 11:59pm
Callbacks: Monday, February 9 at St. Matthew‚Äôs Lutheran Church
 5709 Wedgwood Dr. Fort Worth, TX. 76133

Where to Send Auditions
wedgwoodarts@gmail.com

Email Subject Line
Godspell Audition ‚Äì [Your Name]

WHAT TO SUBMIT
1. Vocal Selection

‚Ä¢ One song, 60‚Äì90 seconds
‚Ä¢ Musical theatre or contemporary style preferred
‚Ä¢ Focus on clear text, musical accuracy, and connection
‚Ä¢ Recorded accompaniment, live accompaniment, or a cappella are all acceptable
‚Ä¢ Singing from Godspell is welcome but not required

2. Audition Side
The following Audition side has 3 parts a Narrot, a father, and a son. Have fun and show us different choices for each voice. We are excited to see your personality, sincerity, and ease with an audience.:

The son ran to meet his father, threw his arms around him, and kissed him, saying: ‚ÄúFather, I have sinned against God and against you; I am no longer fit to be called your son; treat me as one of your paid servants.‚Äù But the father called to one of his servants: ‚ÄúQuick, fetch me my robe, my best one. Put a ring on his finger and shoes on his feet and bring the fatted calf and kill it. And let us have a feast to celebrate the day, for this son of mine was lost and is found.‚Äù And the festivities began!

3. Movement

‚Ä¢ 20‚Äì30 seconds of simple movement
‚Ä¢ Movement to music or light choreography is welcome
‚Ä¢ No dance experience required‚Äîcomfort, rhythm, and willingness to move are what matter most

4. Slate (At the Beginning of Your Video)

Please include:
‚Ä¢ Your name
‚Ä¢ Pronouns (optional)
‚Ä¢ Age range
‚Ä¢ Vocal range (if known)
‚Ä¢ Any instruments you play (if applicable)

5. Video Guidelines

‚Ä¢ One video or multiple videos are fine
‚Ä¢ Phone recordings are perfectly acceptable
‚Ä¢ Neutral background and good lighting recommended
‚Ä¢ Please record each section in one continuous take

6. IN THE EMAIL BODY

First and last name 
Phone number 
Email 
Which parts you are willing to accept 
Any rehearsal conflicts 

REHEARSAL COMMITMENT

Rehearsals begin Monday, February 16 and will be held on Monday and Thursday nights from 7:00‚Äì10:00 PM and Saturdays from 10:00-1:00. 

This process will move intentionally and efficiently from the start, allowing us to create a polished, cohesive production while still building strong ensemble connections. Consistent attendance, preparation, and collaboration are essential.

Tech Week: April 12‚Äì14
Dress Rehearsal: April 16
Performances: April 17‚Äì19

Please audition only if you are able to commit to this schedule.

Godspell is a show rooted in generosity, joy, and shared responsibility. We are eager to bring together a company excited to do focused, meaningful work.

We look forward to seeing your auditions.

ROLES
We are looking for a diverse cast for this show. Performers of any ethnicity, race, color, sex, gender, age, sexual orientation, religion will be considered for the show. 
Jesus: The spiritual and emotional center of the piece. Warm, charismatic, and deeply grounded, with the ability to lead the ensemble through storytelling rather than authority. Strong singer with a gentle, confident presence. 
John the Baptist/Judas: A dual role. John the Baptist opens the show with joyful energy and clarity; Judas evolves into a conflicted, questioning figure. Requires emotional depth, strong acting skills, and vocal diversity. 
We are looking for 8 Actors who fill the following descriptions 
Performer 1: Energetic, playful, and physically expressive. Often drives movement-based storytelling and comic moments. Strong ensemble singer with confidence in unaccompanied sections. 
Performer 2: Bold, charismatic, and impulsive. Often delivers comedic text with sharp timing and physicality. Strong pop/rock vocal presence. 
Performer 3: Thoughtful, gentle, and reflective. Often anchors quieter moments and parables. Warm vocal tone and emotional sincerity. 
Performer 4: Expressive and emotionally open. Often carries lyrical and heartfelt material. Strong singer with the ability to communicate vulnerability. 
Performer 5: Bright, optimistic, and sincere. Frequently leads joyful or playful moments in the ensemble. Clear tone and strong blend. 
Performer 6: Quirky, imaginative, and playful. Comfortable with character work, storytelling, and musical humor. 
Performer 7: Grounded, mature, and emotionally resonant. Often supports dramatic moments with calm authority. Strong musicianship required. 
Performer 8: Confident, dynamic, and expressive. Often takes leadership within group numbers and physical storytelling. Strong rhythmic feel and vocal power.

Actors!. Unleash your creativity and join a vibrant community of passionate filmmakers who are dedicated to bringing stories to life! Together, we'll craft captivating narrative films, forge valuable connections, and fuel our artistic visions. 

This is more than just filmmaking; it's a journey to elevate our craft and careers to new heights! Every Saturday from 4-6 PM near DTLA, we gather to share ideas, collaborate, and inspire one another. If you're truly committed to making an impact in the world of film and ready to embark on this exciting adventure, we invite you to become a part of our filmmaking family. Membership is completely free! 

Complete this form to join us. [https://forms.gle/bb58i1Hc5rzzg2ju7](https://forms.gle/bb58i1Hc5rzzg2ju7?fbclid=IwZXh0bgNhZW0CMTAAYnJpZBExOWgxMkV1M0hERHZPcnRiZHNydGMGYXBwX2lkEDIyMjAzOTE3ODgyMDA4OTIAAR5k9IvyEVLNR7KSIH-49als_mHzt2jmGaMVG-0US9AEEf0j7Noco2gsk8uinQ_aem_Bhp-OAZ6lp-AUQSLYq-m5Q)

Skuespillere i alderen 16-24 √•r samt 30-50 √•r (b√•de m/k) i Aalborg s√∏ges til film for sorgramte unge p√• erhvervsuddannelser üé•

**Hvorn√•r:**

Vi optager nu p√• torsdag og fredag d. 22 og 23. januar i den kommende uge (uge 4) Opgaven er ul√∏nnet, men **transportudgifter** **d√¶kkes** og der vil v√¶re **forplejning p√• set**. 

Kunne du t√¶nke dig at hj√¶lpe med at formidle vigtige budskaber for ansatte og unge p√• erhvervsuddannelser samt f√• erfaring med at v√¶re foran kameraet, s√• l√¶s videre!

items.text:
Ever wonder why actors talk about "objectives," "inner life," and "doing the work"?

These ideas didn't just appear. They were born from a revolution in theatre over 100 years ago, led by one man: Konstantin Stanislavski.

Today, his legacy is being celebrated in a special way: January 17th is his birthday, and it also marks Artist's Day (–î–µ–Ω—å –∞—Ä—Ç–∏—Å—Ç–∞) in Russia. It is a perfect day to honor him and all artists.

Our latest deep dive, "The Origins of Contemporary Acting," is now live. We trace his entire journey:

üé≠ From the star-driven, declamatory theatre of the 1890s.
üß† To Stanislavski's frustrating search for the elusive "creative state."
üèõ To the founding of the Moscow Art Theatre and the birth of realism with Chekhov's The Seagull.
‚öôÔ∏è To the creation of his "System"‚Äîthe structured craft that underpins modern acting from Method to Meisner.

This is more than history; it's the origin story of the tools every actor uses today. If you've ever stepped on a stage or in front of a camera, this will change how you see your craft.

Happy Artist's Day to all creators! To celebrate, explore the legacy of the father of contemporary acting.

Watch or listen the full exploration here: https://youtu.be/f1n-8YQ9Mv4

Today also marks the birthday of Konstantin Stanislavski‚Äîthe father of contemporary acting. His revolutionary "System" is the foundation for nearly all modern acting techniques, from stage to screen.

To understand his direct impact on how we work today, we‚Äôve just released what is essentially a masterclass lecture on his life and legacy. It traces his journey from challenging 19th-century theatre conventions to creating the techniques that define our craft.

Wishing everyone a day filled with inspiration and breakthrough work.

We are casting for an independent drama feature film to be shot in London. We are looking for committed actors for the following roles:

‚∏ª

üé≠ MAIN ROLES

CAMILA
 ‚Ä¢ Gender: Female

 ‚Ä¢ Language: Must speak English + at least one additional language
 ‚Ä¢ Character notes: Strong emotional range, dramatic performance, sensitive and resilient character.

‚∏ª

THOMAS

‚∏ª

‚∏ª

SIMON

‚∏ª

üëÆ SUPPORTING ROLES

‚∏ª

üì© SUBMISSIONS

Hey everyone!

We are now casting **non-union actors** for *An Empty Cup*, a satirical dramedy student short film supported by Vancouver Film School.

This is a **student-led, non-union volunteer production**. While unpaid, the project includes full craft services, catering, and a complimentary professional headshot session for selected performers.

Self-tape submissions open **January 14 at 9:00 AM** and close **January 24 at 11:00 PM**. In-person callbacks will be held on **January 26 from 12:00 PM to 4:00 PM**.

Filming is scheduled for **February 7‚Äì8, 2026** in the **Greater Vancouver Area**.

We are seeking talent for multiple roles with **open ethnicity casting** and encourage performers of all backgrounds to submit. Below, the synopsis of the film and roles of each character are posted.

For more information, please visit our Instagram (@anemptycup_film) or email us at anemptycupfilm@gmail.com.

-An Empty Cup Crew

items.text:
Altarena Playhouse (Alameda, CA) is holding auditions for *‚ÄòNight Mother *by Marsha Norman, Directed by ShawnJ West

 

Performance Dates: May 29th through June 28th     

(Fridays/Saturdays at 7:30 pm, and Sundays at 2:00 pm)

 

SHOW SYNOPSIS:

Thelma Cates is a mother and widow who lives with her daughter, Jessie. Jessie is the divorced mother of a troubled son who struggles with life as an unemployed epileptic. She confesses to her mother that she is going to take her life. Tonight. As Mama pleads with her to reconsider her decision, old secrets are revealed, and long-ignored feelings rise to the surface. The mother-daughter bond between Jessie and Mama becomes stronger and lovelier than ever, making it possible for Jessie to end her noisy, cluttered existence, and take a quieter, calmer path with closure and love.

 

AUDITION DATES:

Monday, January 19th at 7:00pm and Saturday, January 24th at 1:00pm, by appointment

 

Callbacks: Monday, February 2nd, 7-10 pm, by invitation

 

Rehearsals begin April 25, 2026 at 11:00 am

 

Auditions will be held at the Altarena Playhouse, 1409 High Street, Alameda

 

Performers of all races and ethnicities are encouraged to audition.

 

Non-AEA only. $500 Reimbursement for expenses

 

 

CHARACTER DESCRIPTIONS:

THELMA ‚ÄúMAMA‚Äù CATES (Female, 60s)

Warm, talkative, and steeped in the routines of her home life, Thelma is a woman who uses chatter, caretaking, and small comforts to keep the world steady. Beneath her practical exterior, she carries deep anxieties, regrets, and unspoken guilt that surface as the night unfolds. Actors should bring emotional dexterity, humor grounded in truth, and the ability to navigate sharp tonal shifts as Mama confronts an unthinkable situation with both denial and fierce love.

 

JESSIE CATES (Female, 40s)

Direct, methodical, and emotionally contained, Jessie is a woman who has lived with chronic illness, disappointment, and a profound sense of futility. She speaks plainly and acts with quiet determination, revealing a grounded pragmatism rather than melodrama. Actors should bring a nuanced stillness, clarity of intention, and the ability to reveal the powerful internal life beneath Jessie‚Äôs calm, steady presence.

 

To sign up and for audition sides, visit:  [https://www.signupgenius.com/go/9040F4FAFAB28A2F94-61249455-night](https://www.signupgenius.com/go/9040F4FAFAB28A2F94-61249455-night)

 

Please contact Katina at [artisticdirector@altarena.org](mailto:artisticdirector@altarena.org) should you have any questions.

I'm excited to share that the new casting platform, Castingly, is almost at **600 members!** As we prepare to meet with casting directors to showcase the site, I'm actively seeking actors interested in being featured as "example profiles." If you‚Äôd like to participate, please comment below and let me know!

To effectively show off all the site's capabilities, we need users to complete **100% of their profiles.** 

If you're not interested in being showcased but still want to explore the site, you can check us out at [www.castingly.com](http://www.castingly.com/). 

**Membership is free through 2026!** We'll also be rolling out casting breakdowns within the next few weeks. Feel free to reach out if you have any questions!

üï∑Ô∏è FIGHT CHOREOGRAPHER NEEDED ‚Äî FOR BECOMING OUR SPIDER-MAN üï∑Ô∏è

We are looking for a Fight Choreographer for our fan film For Becoming Our Spider-Man, a Miles Morales‚Äìcentered action project.

The film features a major, high-energy action sequence where Miles initially clashes with Hobgoblin (Uncle Aaron) ‚Äî before the two of them ultimately team up to take down larger threats: Shocker and Beetle (Janice Lincoln). This creates a chaotic, fast-paced, and emotionally charged battle that we want to feel cinematic and professional.
You would help choreograph: Rooftop combat between Miles and Hobgoblin that evolves into a partnership.

A dramatic crash through a stained-glass window into a criminal hideout.
Fast, acrobatic Spider-Man-style movement.
A two-versus-two fight as Miles and Hobgoblin take on Shocker and Beetle.
Action moments involving Miles‚Äôs invisibility and bioelectric ‚ÄúVenom‚Äù powers.
We‚Äôre looking for someone who can:
Create clear, exciting, and visually dynamic fight choreography.
Work patiently with young performers.

Prioritize safety while keeping the action intense and believable.

Attend rehearsals on January 22nd, January 25th, and February 9th, ahead of our main shoot on February 11th. 

The location will be in aveley park in Essex 

Experience in martial arts, stage combat, or stunt work is preferred ‚Äî but passion for action filmmaking matters most.
If you‚Äôre interested, please message me via email: ppeterb954@gmail.com please and thank you

We are now casting our Spring show Shake Rattle And Roll and looking for self Contained experienced hardworking performers who are keen to take quality musical shows to the community .The 
The show is a celebration to all the greatest songs and stars of the 50s 60s 70s The Beatles ,Elvis, Doris Day, Connie Francis ,Cliff Richard, Buddy Holly and more.
Dates
Rehearsals- 23rd -27th February 
Playing Dates- 2nd March  -1st  May 
We work Monday to Friday (2 x 60 minute shows per day) 
Casting Breakdown We are now looking for strong /experienced Male and Female singer /performers 
The show is a one man/woman show so we are looking for experienced performers that can hold an audience and are looking for engaging vocalist performers.
We are looking for drivers with cars only .
We are looking for performers on all area of the UK -please include bases when sending details.
We are offering 700 per week plus fuel on the road 
Please send details including a singing reel to info@theentertainmentproviders.co.uk

EXCITING NEWS!

I'm thrilled to share my screenplay/book EDDIE'S BACK - A gripping story that I believe would make a FANTASTIC MOVIE. 

I have already WRITTEN AND COPYRIGHTED THE SCREENPLAY, so it's ready to go! Now I'm reaching out to PRODUCTION COMPANIES , LITERARY AGENTS , FILM AGENTS AND #DIRECTORS who might be interested in bringing this story to life on the big screen.

EDDIE'S BACK - May 1963, Eddie a popular teenager is intentionally hit by a car, which leaves him in a coma. It's 2026, Eddie wakes up. He is shocked and disappointed at what he sees. Until the ghost of JFK visits him and INSPIRES HIM to make a difference.

Now Eddie 79 years young, realizes why he was KEPT ALIVE and what he has to do.

However, a senior Senator with an agenda of his own is watching Eddie's every move and is prepared to stop Eddie's mission at any cost.

DREAM CAST (just imagining!)

#HarrisonFord - #CandyClark - #PaulLeMat - #RichardDreyfuss - #CharlesMartinSmith - #BradleyCooper -#MatthewMcConaughey - #MargotRobbie - #TaylorSwift - #AnneHathaway - #ParisHilton - #JordonHudson - #LaurenSanchez - #AmberHeard - #KrisJenner  #SydneySweeney - #TinaLouise - #CarolBurnett - #ColinHanks - #SenatorJohnKennedy 

DIRECTOR - #RonHoward 

NO OFFICIAL TIES - JUST PUTTING IT OUT THERE AND HOPING TO GET EDDIE'S BACK - INTO THE RIGHT HANDS!

TAGGING TOP AGENCIES: 

@ImageEntertainment - @IndependentArtistGroup - #WilliamMorrisEndeavor - #VerveTalentandLiteraryManagement - #CreativeArtistsAgency - #TheWayneAgency. And Indie powerhouses like: #A24 - #AnnapurnalPictures - #PlanBEntertainment - #BlumHouseProductions - #KillerFilms - #Neon - #FilmNation - #BleeckerStreet - #ElaraPictures - #BigBeach - #APAAgency - #UnitedTalentAgency - #GershAgency - #ArtistsFirst - #IFCFilms - #SonyClassics - #LionsGate 

NO OFFICIAL TIES - Just putting it out there and hoping to get - EDDIE'S BACK into THE RIGHT HANDS!

PRODUCTION COMPANIES I ADMIRE:

#SONYPICTURES - #WARNERBROSDISCOVERY - #IMAGEENTERTAINMENT - #WALTDISNEYPICTURES - #HelloSunshine - #BadRobot - #FifthSeason 

PRODUCERS - I'd love to work with:

#MarkCiardi - #MattDamon - #MarkWahlberg #WillFerrell - #TomHanks - #JeffBezos - #ElonMusk - #ChristineVachon - #TeddySchwarzman - #NinaYangBongiovi #LenaWaithe 

NO OFFICIAL TIES - JUST PUTTING IT OUT THERE. HOPING TO GET (EDDIE'S BACK) INTO THE RIGHT HANDS.

I'd also like to catch the eye of DIRECTORS like: #StevenSpielberg - #RonHoward - #StevenSoderbergh - #ToscaMusk - #RyleeScott - #SofiaCoppola - #GeorgeLucas - #BenStiller 

Their storytelling I admire deeply.

No Official ties - Just hoping to catch the eye of these incredible teams.

If you know someone in the film or media who might love this concept, please feel free to REACH OUT or SHARE THIS POST. 

IMDB.ME  https://pro.imdb.com/name/nm4381966

LET'S MAKE MOVIE MAGIC HAPPEN!

#EDDIE'S BACK #BooktoFilm #Screenplayready #FilmAdaptation #Moviepitch #Filmmakers #Independantfilm #IndieCinema #literaryagents

*DIGITAL ART OPEN-CALL OPPORTUNITY IN NYC*

Start the new year by exhibiting your work **on Madison Ave** in NYC. This one-night digital art show at a five-level speakeasy art studio inside Herbwell, seeks artworks exploring **rebirth, evolution, endings, beginnings, and transformation**. Showcase your art in the same neighborhood as monumental museums and galleries like the MoMa.

All digital mediums welcome: Digital Paintings & Illustration, 3D Modeling & Digital Sculpture, Digital Collage & Vector Art, Digital Photography, Pixel Art, GIF Art / Animation, Glitch Art, Generative Art, Augmented Reality (AR) Art, Virtual Reality (VR) Art, AI Art, Mixed Media (with digital components), Video Art & Motion Graphics, NFTs & Blockchain-Backed Works, Interactive & Installation-Based Digital Works, Derivative works (where you hold rights to exhibit), Scanned Physical Works

**Why submit?**

‚Ä¢ Showcase your work in one of NYC‚Äôs most prestigious art corridors
‚Ä¢ Photos, documentation, and press coverage included
‚Ä¢ Connect with curators, collectors, and international artists
‚Ä¢ Feature in a multi-disciplinary event blending digital art, traditional art, and live music

If your work speaks to stepping into something new ‚Äî we‚Äôd love to see it.

**Apply here:** [https://hug.art/open-calls/New-Year-Exhibition-on-Madison-Ave-in-NYC](https://hug.art/open-calls/New-Year-Exhibition-on-Madison-Ave-in-NYC)

sharedPost.text: In the 1990's I worked with a chap named Paul Collis. He became an actor and starred in Miss Saigon at the Theatre Royal Drury Lane and later in Phantom of the Opera. We saw him in Miss Saigon and were invited backstage afterwards. We have a beautifully framed copy of the event poster signed by the entire cast. When we went to Phantom he did not perform because he had been taken ill. Tragically he passed away shortly afterwards. Even worse he had just had a child. I have made several attempts to trace his Widow (via Equity, googling etc) but had zero response. I did not know her name but my reason is that I would like to pass on the poster as a memory of Paul. Any ideas? I am a bit stumped.

topComments.text: I have found more details: his wife‚Äôs and daughter‚Äôs and parents‚Äô names but am rather loathe to share - I do want to believe what he says but I can‚Äôt confirm it. Has he tried contacting Cameron Mackintosh‚Äôs company? - his wife continued her career so it may have details or can pass on a message https://www.cameronmackintosh.com/ I am not being self righteous but it was so easy to find details & he could have contacted The Stage - it would be a nice little story with an image of the poster. I understand he may have worked with Paul outside showbiz and all may be genuine but details were so easy to find. I even know the area where she was living some years ago. I have now removed details of his home town & parents home just in case, altho‚Äô it is in the public domain. He has put the same message in searching people groupsÔøº rather than musical theatre/actors‚Äô groups and he‚Äôs very vague - signing a poster seems to give the impression he was connected with the theatre show. The poster is from Hitchin  where Paul Collis was apparently a church chorister according to a post from someone else.

items.text:
Casting Call (Non-Union) for ALL AGES, ALL DEMOGRAPHICS - Paid

Looking for actors to play the role of a client in a simulated therapy session. The video clips will be used in an online training system for counselors and psychologists. The sessions include some scripted elements to prepare, and then some improv with prompts.

All ages, all gender expressions/identities, all ethnicities, and persons with disabilities are welcome. 

All experience levels with acting are welcome. We are committed to making this a respectful and safe process, with open communication and respect for boundaries.

Comfortable English fluency is required.

Immediate filming dates are January 22 to February 6, based on actor availability, but our needs are ongoing and more will occur in the future, so please submit if you're interested at all.

Location is downtown Vancouver - Gastown. Pay is $60 CAD per hour, with the expectation of some prepared material, studio session duration: 1-2 hours. If there is some significant preparation required, compensation is offered for that time.

Please email phil@skillsetter.com with your headshot and resume, as well as some information about you, such as gender identity, age, cultural/racial background. If you've submitted for a past session, you're welcome to submit again. We do sometimes receive more submissions than we are able to respond to, but we do read them all, and we do save your submissions for future consideration.

Vom 09.02.2026 - 22.05.2026 findet in der Schnitt-Akademie Berlin der n√§chste gro√üe Kompaktkurs Filmschnitt f√ºr alle statt, die sich in den technischen und dramaturgischen Bereichen des Filmschnitts weiterbilden wollen: https://www.schnitt-akademie.de/kompaktkurse.php?KursID=100

Der Kurs findet komplett in Form von Online-Unterricht statt, man kann also von jedem beliebigen Ort aus daran teilnehmen. Er dauert 3,5 Monate, Mo-Fr jeweils von 09:00-17:00. 

**Die Weiterbildung kann mit einem Bildungsgutschein der Agentur f√ºr Arbeit (100%-F√∂rderung, auch f√ºr Firmen und Besch√§ftigte) oder durch die EU-F√∂rderung KOMPASS (90%-F√∂rderung, f√ºr Solo-Selbst√§ndige) finanziert werden .** 

Inhalte des Kurses: 

- AVID Mediacomposer

- DaVinci Resolve

- Adobe Premiere Pro

- After Effects

- Spiel- u. Dokumentarfilmschnitt

- Schnitt von TV-News und Reportagen

- Codecs, Imports, Exports und Workflows

- Schnitt u. Sound

- Dramaturgie, Rhythmus und Gestaltung

- Schnitt-Assistenz

- Musikschnitt

- Colorgrading

- Vertrags- u. Urheberrecht

Die Anmeldung l√§uft, es gibt zur Zeit noch Pl√§tze: https://www.schnitt-akademie.de/kompaktkurse.php?KursID=100

***FREE SOLO SHOW CLASS THIS SATURDAY ***

Hello Acting Community!

Are you curious about creating a ONE PERSON SHOW?

Then you do not want to miss this 100% FREE, 100% AWESOME solo theatre class "The Art of Creating the One Person Show" commencing THIS SAT JANUARY 17th @10AM (PST)/12pm (CST)/1pm (EST) via Zoom.

RSVP HERE: [https://www.soaringsolostudios.com/free-one-person-play-class/](https://www.soaringsolostudios.com/free-one-person-play-class/)

I have been teaching this ongoing FREE class for over a decade and I have been working in the genre of Solo Theatre for over 20 years. I have directed & developed well over 175 solo shows and toured successfully with my own award-winning solo shows, and I would be honored and excited to help guide YOU into your own success as a Solo Artist.

Personnel Secretary position:

**Job Title:** Personnel Secretary( open minded)
**Location:** gurgram 
**Job Type:** Full-time

**About Us:**

Kuber picture and craft is a leading company seeking an experienced Personnel Secretary to join our team.

**Job Summary:**

We are looking for a highly organized and efficient Personnel Secretary to provide administrative support to our management team. The ideal candidate will have excellent communication skills, proficiency in MS Office, and the ability to maintain confidentiality.

**Responsibilities:**

- Provide administrative support to management team
- Coordinate travel arrangements, meetings, and events.

- Maintain confidential files and records
- Prepare correspondence, reports, and presentations.

- Develop and implement effective filing systems.

- Coordinate recruitment and training programs

**Requirements:**

- 2+ years of experience as a Personnel Secretary or similar role
- Proficiency in MS Office and Google Suite

- Excellent communication and interpersonal skills

- Ability to maintain confidentiality

- Strong organizational and time management skills

**What We Offer:**

- Competitive salary: ‚Çπ90,000/month
- Opportunity to work with a dynamic team
- Professional growth and development

**How to Apply:**

If you are a motivated and organized individual who is passionate about providing exceptional administrative support, please submit your application, including your resume and cover letter, to email id kuberpicture1305@gmail.com

**Casting Call - 1970s Biographical Feature Film**

For a new biographical feature film set in the 1970s, we are looking for **MEN aged approx. 20-35, up to 180 cm max., **an athletic build. In role** future MILITARY PERSONNEL**.

Gentlemen of the following origins are particularly welcome:
* **CUBANS**
* **MONGOLIANS**
* **BULGARIANS**
* **HULGARIANS**

**Shooting Days:**
* February 5 ‚Äì shooting in Warsaw
* March 18 ‚Äì shooting in Warsaw
* March 26 ‚Äì shooting in Pi≈Ça (transport and hotel provided)
* May 1 ‚Äì shooting likely in Warsaw (TBC)

**Rate: 450 PLN per shooting day**

**Characterization Guidelines:**
* Absolutely no tattoos
* Hair must be short, but cut without the use of clippers
* No facial hair (clean-shaven)
* Athletic build

**Please send applications to:** **ewelina.wika@podtytulem.pl**
**Subject Line:** **KKZ**
**Email Content:** Name and surname, age, phone number, city/town of residence, nationality + measurements: height, chest, waist, hips, clothing and shoe size.
**Attachment:** **PHOTO OF FACE AND FIGURE: taken only on the day of application + profile photo**

**FACE PHOTO** ‚Äì portrait selfie in daylight, straight-on, looking into the lens. No filters. No glasses. No head covering.
**FIGURE PHOTO** ‚Äì in clothing that shows the outline of the figure.

Casting : "Maybe its love, maybe not"

I am Thomas Goersch from Stuttgart Germany. 
Actor and Filmdirector. 
I am making Independent Movies.
I present my movies on International Film festivals and was lucky to receive some awards. 
But the work is not about awards and money, its about making movies for the people to think about.
My next movie is a modern love story:
An elderly man is meeting another younger, very attractive man in the Internet.  But they are from different Continents. They start a long distance relastionship ship. which is full of passion and desire. 
One day the younger man starts to ask for money, cause he is a Student and no more able to pay his bills. 
The older man is full of distrust.
Is he only there  to pay his lovers bills or is there love between them ?
A story with two endings.
One with true love and one with betrayl.
I am looking for the young attraktive Lover.
Men  25 to 42 years old,  good looking  who is able to film his parts on his own by smartshone
I am always open and honest. You can earn no money on this. but maybe there is a good film in the end promoting for you.
I guess its not necessary that an educated actor is playing this part. so feel free to get in touch
Thats me 
www.imdb.com/name/nm1591928
Get in touch under Thomas.Goersch@vodafonemail.de 
please ask for details.

# **VI S√òGER STATISTER **

Vi s√∏ger featured statister M/K/NB i alderen 28-45 til en kortfilm af Agnes Trier. Castet inkluderer Filippa Coster-Waldau, Jacob Lohmann, Olivia Joof, Sidsel Siem Koch og Kitt Maiken Mortensen. 

Pitch

Emma er midt i tyverne og utilpas i rollen som nybagt mor. Til et for√¶ldrem√∏de i vuggestuen m√• Emma g√∏re op med sig selv hvor langt hun vil g√• for at skjule sine sande f√∏lelser.

Tristans mor er en karakterunders√∏gelse af en ung kvinde i en s√•rbar periode.

Praktisk info:

Du skal spille en for√¶ldre i for√¶ldregruppen, s√• det vigtigt du kan deltage i optagelser hele dagen d. 24/1+25/1 i tidsrummet 8-18, og meget gerne ogs√• en halv dag i aftentimerne mandag. d. 26/1.

Erfaring med improvisation og replikker er en fordel, men ikke et 

krav.

Jobbet er ul√∏nnet men vi s√∏ger for forplejning og god energi. 

Vi filmer i Sydhavnen.

Ved interesse send vellignende billede, samt navn, alder og erfaring til casting@adomeitfilm.com

items.text:
# **VI S√òGER STATISTER **

Vi s√∏ger featured statister M/K/NB i alderen 28-45 til en kortfilm af Agnes Trier. Castet inkluderer Filippa Coster-Waldau, Jacob Lohmann, Olivia Joof, Sidsel Siem Koch og Kitt Maiken Mortensen. 

Pitch

Emma er midt i tyverne og utilpas i rollen som nybagt mor. Til et for√¶ldrem√∏de i vuggestuen m√• Emma g√∏re op med sig selv hvor langt hun vil g√• for at skjule sine sande f√∏lelser.

Tristans mor er en karakterunders√∏gelse af en ung kvinde i en s√•rbar periode.

Praktisk info:

Du skal spille en for√¶ldre i for√¶ldregruppen, s√• det vigtigt du kan deltage i optagelser hele dagen d. 24/1+25/1 i tidsrummet 8-18, og meget gerne ogs√• en halv dag i aftentimerne mandag. d. 26/1.

Erfaring med improvisation og replikker er en fordel, men ikke et 

krav.

Jobbet er ul√∏nnet men vi s√∏ger for forplejning og god energi. 

Vi filmer i Sydhavnen.

Ved interesse send vellignende billede, samt navn, alder og erfaring til casting@adomeitfilm.com

Casting : "Maybe its love, maybe not"

I am Thomas Goersch from Stuttgart Germany. 
Actor and Filmdirector. 
I am making Independent Movies.
I present my movies on International Film festivals and was lucky to receive some awards. 
But the work is not about awards and money, its about making movies for the people to think about.
My next movie is a modern love story:
An elderly man is meeting another younger, very attractive man in the Internet.  But they are from different Continents. They start a long distance relastionship ship. which is full of passion and desire. 
One day the younger man starts to ask for money, cause he is a Student and no more able to pay his bills. 
The older man is full of distrust.
Is he only there  to pay his lovers bills or is there love between them ?
A story with two endings.
One with true love and one with betrayl.
I am looking for the young attraktive Lover.
Men  25 to 42 years old,  good looking  who is able to film his parts on his own by smartshone
I am always open and honest. You can earn no money on this. but maybe there is a good film in the end promoting for you.
I guess its not necessary that an educated actor is playing this part. so feel free to get in touch
Thats me 
www.imdb.com/name/nm1591928
Get in touch under Thomas.Goersch@vodafonemail.de 
please ask for details.

Stop Stage Fright in 10 seconds!

New FREE Resource: The FBI Reset Toolkit: a Downloadable Backstage Companion for Performers from Beyond The Spotlight Psychology.

For performers, the moments right before stepping on stage are often the most vulnerable.

Warm-ups can fade, techniques can slip and anxiety takes the spotlight.

That‚Äôs why I‚Äôve packaged the FBI Reset into a portable, backstage-ready toolkit you can download and keep on your phone.

What‚Äôs inside the free toolkit:

üéß Downloadable Audio Guide: A clean, FBI Reset audio track (F=Feet, B=Breath, I=Intention) enhanced with calming music - ready to use offline, anytime nerves strike.

üìò Companion PDF Guide: A detailed walkthrough of the science and a practice protocol to integrate the reset into your pre-show routine.

üéØ Exclusive Bonus: The Stage Fright Symptom Profiler - a diagnostic tool to help you identify your unique anxiety patterns and tailor your coping strategies.

I am really passionate about giving all of you - stage performing artists a clinical tool in your pocket when you need it most.

It is perfect for musicians, singers, actors, speakers, and anyone who faces performance pressure.

‚¨áÔ∏è Download your free copy here https://www.beyondthespotlightpsychology.co.uk/freebie-stage-profiler-sign-up-page

I‚Äôd love to hear how it works for you backstage.

Feel free to share with colleagues who may benefit from it. Thank you.

Dr Maja Jankowska, Clinical & Counselling Psychologist

Beyond The Spotlight Psychology
